metadata.name: The Managed Miles - part 1 #279
metadata.description:
A bespoke literary chance machine, crafted from a matrix of ranked, hand-crafted options.
The style and tone of the generated output influences the title, to match the poem as closely as possible.

Based on an original poem in four verses. This is part 1 (plus title). 
Parts 2-4 releasing concurrently.

The algorithm that drives the poem is an evolving feature map. Each word has a series of features that, when selected, contribute to the selection of the following words.

In this way, the poem evolves in a way that is deterministic but with very random roots. 

The chance of two transactions generating the same poem from the system is about 1 in 450,000.

Wily Guys [ T : @guyswily / W : wilyguys.com / I : @wilyguys / M : wilyguys.medium.com ]

metadata.name: Precision: angles #44
metadata.description:
This is the first hash-derived entry into my "Precisions" series.  I have been using Precisions as a meditative art practice where I focus on exact positioning of elements, less-emphasized colors, and repetition of geometric shapes.  

In "angles", each element is comprised of right triangles transformed over a common point.  I decided to bring some of the fragmentation from my previous project, "Restrictions", to produce irregular works.  I found beauty in that unpredictable asymmetry and feel it really enhances the structure of this piece.

metadata.name: (fx)moji #31
metadata.description:
Emoji is the word for visual language, a way to express emotion without words.

From its humble origins as a Japanese emoticon in the mid-1990s, they exploded in popularity when appeared as a critical part of Apple's iPhone launch in 2007. The internationalization of emoji is an inexorable force, and today it is almost impossible to send a message without using one.

Emojis evolved as a way to communicate quickly and easily, and now they will evolve one more time and become an NFT generative art reborn as (fx)moji where basic geometric forms create a new full set of emojis expressions.

32 emojis,
7 Animations,
6 Color &
Infinite expressions 😊

Made with love ❤️ 🧡 💛 💚 💙 and p5js

metadata.name: PEGS #206
metadata.description: Taking inspiration from work by Karl Gerstner, Armin Hofmann, Nick Kuder and Dmitri Cherniak, PEGS explores the limits of constrained algorithmic variation. Based on the simple, playful idea of wrapping a string across a board of pegs, it shows how endless possibilities can be achieved with just a basic set of rules and a few primary colors. When done right, generative art challenges us to answer fundamental questions around creativity, beauty, and life itself.
